How did you migrate to 3.2?  Did you install 3.2 on top of the existing 3.1 install?  Are there any errors in the log from *before* restarting the computer - your first session run with 3.2?

You may be able to restart this workspace by deleting/renaming the file workspace/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.core.resources/.snap.

Updating bug title - the NoClassDefFoundError is a side-effect of the resources plugin failing to start. The root of the startup failure is the ObjectNotFoundException while rerooting the tree after applying the snapshot.
